Class PersistentSet<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>,R extends java.lang.Comparable<R>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • PersistentSet<E,R>

  • public class PersistentSet<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>,R extends java.lang.Comparable<R>>
extends java.lang.Object
    A Persistent Implementation of a Left Leaning RedBlack Tree as a Set. Takes a revision based approach to persistence, where the revision may be any comparable. Parameterized by E, the element type to store, and R, the revision. Both must extend java.lang.Comparable. This set assumes that the tree is built with non-decreasing revisions. Altering past revisions will not cause cascading changes to future revisions.
